Hi, FWIW I'm dealing with a similar issue in FeinCMS (and reversion).
I've found that using is_popup in a template (as FeinCMS still does) gets caught out when the Save button is clicked.  
```
{% block content %}
    {% with 1 as is_popup %}
        {{block.super}}
    {% endwith %}
{% endblock %}
```
This catch is in Reversion 2.0's use of `changeform_view()` and thereby `response_change()` which then tries to return a view for the popup without extra_content  - which means that when `_reversion_revisionform_view` changes the template back to `revision_form.html`  it doesn't have the extra_context it needs so errors (with a NoReverseMatch error rendering  breadcrumbs without `app_label` or `opts`

I don't think there's anything to be fixed in Reversion, but products (like FeinCMS) that depend on it need to stop using `is_popup` in block content.

HTH 

See https://github.com/feincms/feincms/issues/661

