@riyadparvez : to complement @ltfish 's answer, we currently provide two implementations of DDG (Data Dependence Graphs) in Angr: one of them relies on the states computed by the CFG (the analysis is mostly static, meaning that most expressions are not evaluated), and the other one does it on top of the value flow graph (VFG), which is an augmented form of CFG based on VSA[1].

Both these implementations compute def-use chains, and the code is located in analysis/ddg.py and analysis/vsa_ddg.py respectively.

[1] https://research.cs.wisc.edu/wpis/papers/balakrishnan_thesis.pdf

