@KerstinKeller That's a good point about `include(pybind11Tools)`. 

@loriab I see pybind11Tools is already included in the config, but I'm guessing the extra include is required because of variable scope. In that case, the [cache variables](https://github.com/pybind/pybind11/pull/506/files#diff-af3b638bc2a3e6c650974192a53c7291R26) should just be moved from `CMakeLists.txt` into `pybind11Tools.cmake` to make everything work.

If `CMAKECONFIG_INSTALL_DIR` is made a `CACHE` variable, it should be prefixed with `PYBIND11_`.

We definitely want to [improve the project's README](#29) and should add some real documentation.

However I doubt man pages are the correct way to distribute this documentation since I got the feeling they are very uncommon in the Python ecosystem, especially for packages distributed via PyPI. Tobias just suggested [readthedocs.org](https://readthedocs.org/) to publish documentation and I'd prefer that idea.

@oberstet: In case somebody should ever find any time to actually write some documentation, do you think man pages are worth investigating? [Sphinx](http://www.sphinx-doc.org/en/stable/man/sphinx-build.html) seems actually be able to build man pages, so it might be possible with an acceptable amount of effort, but I'd say man pages are too specific to the *nix world to be generally useful.

